Package grafioschtrader.gtnet.handler.impl

Class ServerlistResponseHandler

java.lang.Object
grafioschtrader.gtnet.handler.AbstractGTNetMessageHandler
grafioschtrader.gtnet.handler.AbstractResponseHandler
grafioschtrader.gtnet.handler.impl.ServerlistResponseHandler
All Implemented Interfaces:
GTNetMessageHandler
@Component public class ServerlistResponseHandler extends AbstractResponseHandler
Handler for server list response messages (accept and reject). Processes both GT_NET_UPDATE_SERVERLIST_ACCEPT_S and GT_NET_UPDATE_SERVERLIST_REJECTED_S responses. When accepted, the response includes a list of known servers in the payload. This handler processes the list and adds any new servers to the local GTNet table (if allowServerCreation is enabled on our own entry).

    • getSupportedMessageCode

      public GTNetMessageCodeType getSupportedMessageCode()
      Description copied from interface: GTNetMessageHandler
      Returns the primary message code this handler is responsible for. For handlers supporting multiple codes, this returns the first/primary code. Override GTNetMessageHandler.getSupportedMessageCodes() to register all supported codes.

    • getSupportedMessageCodes

      public Set<GTNetMessageCodeType> getSupportedMessageCodes()
      Description copied from interface: GTNetMessageHandler
      Returns all message codes this handler can process. Override this method to handle multiple related message codes in a single handler. The default implementation returns only the single code from GTNetMessageHandler.getSupportedMessageCode().
      Returns:
      set of supported message codes

    • processResponseSideEffects

      protected void processResponseSideEffects(GTNetMessageContext context, GTNetMessage storedMessage)
      Description copied from class: AbstractResponseHandler
